article.description: Jayden Gardner had 22 points as East Carolina topped Campbell 79-67 on Saturday.
article.headline: Gardner lifts East Carolina past Campbell 79-67
article.linkText: Gardner lifts East Carolina past Campbell 79-67
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. -- Jayden Gardner had 22 points as East Carolina topped Campbell 79-67 on Saturday. Gardner hit 14 of 16 from the free throw line. Brandon Suggs had 16 points for East Carolina (3-7), which snapped its four-game losing streak. J.J. Miles added 12 points. Tristen Newton had 11 points for the hosts. Cedric Henderson Jr. had 18 points for the Fighting Camels (6-3). Milos Stajcic added 11 points. Austin McCullough had 11 points. East Carolina plays Maryland Eastern Shore at home on Tuesday. Campbell takes on Elon at home on Tuesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
